This article is a summary of an executive order issued by President Joe Biden on January 21, 2021, regarding public health measures to prevent the spread of COVID-19. The order mandates the wearing of masks in airports, commercial aircraft, trains, public maritime vessels, intercity bus services, and all forms of public transportation. It also calls for additional public health measures for domestic travel and international travel, including requiring travelers to produce proof of a recent negative COVID-19 test prior to entry into the United States. The order emphasizes coordination between relevant agencies and encourages the implementation of CDC guidelines.